rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be amazing! As it just started, there's a lot to be looking forward too! My friend recently has been placed on lockdown again, so I'll be spending a lot of time hanging out with him. (digitally.) Otherwise, I have some work to do this week, but I really enjoy my side project!
critical_positive: My conversation partner was very outgoing & didn't hold my fear/shyness against me. This being the first time I did something like this, It was nice that she was patient & treated my fairly. From what we discussed, we had quite a bit in common! It was nice meeting someone random & engaging with them! I was trying to suggest she play Minecraft with her whole family, as I believe the game could help them all find something that they would all enjoy.
critical_negative: Honestly, the only thing that didn't really work out well was me. I'm pretty shy, so this was a huge change of pace for me. It was a little stressful. I think I probably slowed the conversation down most of the time. Otherwise, she had some sort of alarm that would go off periodically, but it wasn't that bad. (Lol.)

rest_of_day_open: I see my week going well. Work-wise, I think I'll be productive, which is always a good thing. I plan on doing some fun activities with my kids, so that should be fun. We don't have a lot of set things we have to do, so it is pretty laid back.
critical_positive: When we found some common areas to discuss, it seemed to go a little better. Talking about his dog and the video games he likes to play made him more talkative. I tried to adjust and relate as much as I could, which I do think he appreciated. We laughed some.
critical_negative: There was a little awkwardness with the discussion of 1st-person shooter games and with Bouvier dogs being smarter than shepherds. Totally fine - just a little awkward. I felt like I had to carry the conversation a little more. He was definitely shy and a bit uncomfortable. I may have overcompensated too much.
